<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Key: D major (2 sharps). This carol is often performed in minor — the ABC lead sheet
  annotates some non-diatonic chords (Am, Eb, C). All substituted with nearest diatonic:
  Am -> Em (ii); Eb -> D (I); C -> G (IV); treated as color in the melody only.
- Verse (bars 1-8): Light 2-note RH, 4-note LH. Em and D alternate as the main pillars.
- Refrain (bars 9-16): Fuller texture, 3-note RH at climax (bars 9, 13). LH same weight.
- Bar 8: V→ii cadence (A→Em) unusual — authentic cadence to tonic minor region.
  Retained as a strong expressional moment.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Bars 7-8: RH descends G→E→E while LH moves Em→Bm→A→Em — inner voice motion
  follows the modal quality of the piece.
- Bar 12: Melody drops from F# to D to B (low) — LH provides full D open voicing
  as harmonic anchor while melody leaps down an octave.
- Bar 16: Final A→Em cadence: RH expands to 3-note Em chord at close.

TEXTURE ARC:
- Bars 0-8: Sparse 2-note RH throughout verse.
- Bars 9-12: Refrain opens with 3-note RH at D5 peak (bar 9, 13).
- Bars 13-16: Maintain full texture through second refrain, final Em close.
-->
